block content
  #grid.main-content
    .row.content
      .twelve.columns.content
        h1 How to Update MareshiaDonald.com
    .row.content
      .twelve.columns.content
        p.no-top-margin On this page, I'll describe the the workflow of updating the website mareshiadonald.com. I will attempt to be as detailed as possible by listing the software that you'll need; how to download the current site's content; the files that you may want to edit; templates for editing particular sections; and how to upload to the site.
    .row.content
      .twelve.columns.content
        h2 Software
        hr
        dl
          dt
            strong 
              a(href="https://filezilla-project.org/download.php?type=client") FileZilla
          dd
            em This is the software that you will be using to connect to the server located at mareshiadonald.com. Filezilla is an FTP (File Transfer Protocol) application. It allows you to view and update files on an FTP server in the same way you would view and update files on your own computer.
           dt
            strong 
              a(href="http://brackets.io/") Brackets
          dd
            | This is my personal favorite text editor for coding. This application will let you open up any of your website files and edit them. It works just like a regular text editor but does some smart color coding for editing code. If you don't like brackets, you may want to try 
            strong
              a(href="http://www.sublimetext.com/") Sublime Text
            |.
        h3 
          strong Setting up Filezilla 
        ol
          li 
            | After you've downloaded filezilla for the first time, open the application and you should see this screen
            img.center(src="/public/images/how-to/1filezilla.png")
          li
            | Click the Site Maganger link
            img(src="/public/images/how-to/2filezilla.png")
          li 
            | Click 
            strong New Site
            |  and enter your information like below. You should already know your password and username. Click 
            strong Connect 
            | and that will save your settings and connect to the server.
            dl
              dt 
                strong Host
              dd ftp.mareshiadonald.com
            img(src="/public/images/how-to/3filezilla.png")
          li If you get a message prompting you to trust the servers certificate, click 
            strong ok
            |  .
          li 
            | Select every file and save it in a folder on your computer (if you want, you can download a copy of the website from the last time adam edited 
            strong
              a(href="https://github.com/apere/mar/archive/master.zip") here
            | . This folder is the entire contents of your website. This is where you'll be working from.
    .row.content
      .twelve.columns.content
        h2 Files
        hr
        dl
          dt
            h3
              strong /public/images/
          dd
            | All images belong in this folder. If you want to swap out an image, I suggest naming it the same as the image you're replacing and swap the files.
          dt
            h3
              strong index.html
          dd
            | Every webpage will have a filename of "index.html". This one, the one in the main folder, is the file for 
            strong MareshiaDonald.com/
          dd
            img(src="/public/images/how-to/4index.png")
          dd 
            p To find the areas that you'll want to edit, look for <strong>inner-wrapper</strong>. Inside of <strong>inner-wrapper</strong>, the two places that you'll want to edit are: 
            ol
              li
                dl
                  dt
                    | title : 
                    code <strong>&lt;h1&gt;</strong> [ insert title ] <strong>&lt;/h1&gt;</strong>
                  dd
                    | e.g. 
                    em Mareshia Donald, PhD
              li
                dt
                  | phrase : 
                  code <strong>&lt;h2&gt;</strong> [ insert phrase ] <strong>&lt;/h2&gt;</strong>
                dd
                  | e.g. 
                  em Scientist, STEM Educator and Outreach Professional with a commitment to social justice and diversifying the STEM pipeline.
          dd
            pre
              code
                | &lt;div class=&quot;<strong>inner-wrapper</strong>&quot;&gt;
                |   <strong>&lt;h1&gt;</strong>Mareshia Donald, PhD<strong>&lt;/h1&gt;</strong>
                |   <strong>&lt;h5&gt;</strong>Scientist, STEM Educator and Outreach Professional with a commitment to social justice and diversifying the STEM pipeline.<strong>&lt;/h5&gt;</strong>
                | &lt;/div&gt;
          dt 
            h3
              strong /about/index.html
          dd
            p This is the file for 
              strong MareshiaDonald.com/about/
          dd
            img(src="/public/images/how-to/5about.png")
          dd 
            p To find the areas that you'll want to edit, look for the title of the section you want to edit
            ol
              li
                dl
                  dt
                    | Personal Statement : 
                    code <strong>&lt;p&gt;</strong> [ insert personal statement ] <strong>&lt;/p&gt;</strong>
                  dd
                    | e.g. 
                    em Basic science exists as a language and a culture&hellip;
              
                  dd
                    pre
                      code
                        | &lt;h2&gt;Personal Statement&lt;/h2&gt;
                        |   <strong>&lt;p&gt;</strong>Basic science exists as a language and a culture all its own. I am a translator and a cultural ambassador. I am a quick learner who possesses strong analytic skills, a collaborative spirit, and a passion for developing new skills and meeting new people. I am fortunate to work in an environment in which I'm exposed to the broad applications of STEM. I am familiar with research and literature in an array of disciplines within the life sciences. I am passionate about communicating science and increasing entry points to educational access especially to under-resourced populations. I look forward to leveraging my scientific training to promote scientific literacy and shape the future of scientific innovation.</strong>&lt;/p&gt;</strong>
              li
                dl
                  dt
                    | Overview of Qualifications: 
                    code <strong>&lt;li&gt; &lt;strong&gt;</strong> [ insert bold word ] <strong>&lt;/strong&gt;</strong> [ insert rest of statement ] <strong>&lt;/li&gt;</strong>
                  dd
                    | e.g. 
                    em Basic science exists as a language and a culture&hellip;
              
                  dd
                    pre
                      code
                        | &lt;h2&gt;Overview of Qualifications&lt;/h2&gt;
                        |   &lt;ul&gt;
                        |     <strong>&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;</strong>Concept driven<strong>&lt;/strong&gt;</strong> trained empiricist proficient at evaluating, understanding and communicating basic science<strong>&lt;/li&gt;</strong>
                        |     &lt;li&gt;Experienced in developing &lt;strong&gt; fun and accessible science curriculum &lt;/strong&gt;for under-resourced middle- and high school students&lt;/li&gt;
                        |     &lt;li&gt;10+ years of experience with a wide range of techniques in basic &lt;strong&gt; laboratory research and data analysis&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
                        |     &lt;li&gt; &lt;/li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Accomplished teacher to diverse audiences&lt;/strong&gt;, grade 6 through university level
                        |     &lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Capable communicator &lt;/strong&gt; with a demonstrated ability to work in diverse, collaborative and dynamic environments&lt;/li&gt;
                        |     &lt;li&gt;Effective &lt;strong&gt;grant and fellowship writer&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
                        |     &lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Creative and innovative thinker &lt;/strong&gt;and advocate for interdisciplinary, innovative STEM Education.&lt;/li&gt;
                        |   &lt;/ul&gt;
            h3
              strong /awards-honors-press/index.html
          dd
            | This is the file for 
            strong MareshiaDonald.com/awards-honors-press/
          dd
            img(src="/public/images/how-to/6awards.png")
          dd 
            p To find the areas that you'll want to edit, look for the section title
            ol
              li
                dl
                  dt
                    | Awards & Honors : <br>
                    code <strong>&lt;dt&gt;&lt;strong&gt;</strong> [insert award/honor title] <strong>&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/dt&gt;</strong><br>
                    code <strong>&lt;dd class=&quot;date&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;</strong> [insert date ]<strong>&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/dd&gt;</strong>
                    
                  dd
                    | e.g. 
                    em 
                      | American Physiological Society William Townsend Porter Physiology Fellowship<br>September 2010 - September 2012
                  dd
                    pre
                      code
                        | &lt;h2&gt;Awards &amp; Honors&lt;/h2&gt;
                        | &lt;dl class=&quot;<strong>awards</strong>&quot;&gt;
                        |   <strong>&lt;dt&gt;&lt;strong&gt;</strong>American Physiological Society William Townsend Porter Physiology Fellowship <strong>&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/dt&gt;</strong>
                        |   <strong>&lt;dd class=&quot;date&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;</strong>September 2010 - September 2012<strong>&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/dd&gt;</strong>
                        |   &lt;dt&gt;&lt;strong&gt;American Psychological Association Diversity Program in Neuroscience Pre-Doctoral Fellowship&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/dt&gt;
